\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks-handlers/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"c7d98986-07d3-49fd-8a13-bb0209d3d94c\",\"toolUseID\":\"c7d98986-07d3-49fd-8a13-bb0209d3d94c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:43:08.853Z\",\"uuid\":\"41ff432e-2940-49d0-bcbc-7a5a4e05b305\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"41ff432e-2940-49d0-bcbc-7a5a4e05b305\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"f5a18f53-b820-45d5-8712-dd771912e7d9\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"agile-twirling-flask\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: E2E Triage Skill — Add Local Mode + CI Re-runs\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe current e2e-triage skill is CI-only: it downloads artifacts from a failed GitHub Actions run and classifies failures based on static artifact analysis. This has two problems:\\n\\n1. **CI mode lacks re-run verification** — classification relies on heuristic signals (timeout patterns, error strings) rather than actually re-running the test to see if it reproduces.\\n2. **No local triage path** — when a user wants to triage failures locally, they must manually run tests and interpret results. The skill should support `mise run test:e2e` for local re-runs.\\n\\n**Goal:** Enhance the single SKILL.md with two modes (auto-detected) and add re-run verification to both.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md` | Rewrite with dual-mode (local + CI), re-run logic, updated classification |\\n| `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` | Add `actions: write` permission, increase timeout to 60m, update Claude prompt |\\n\\n**No changes needed:**\\n- `.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml` — already has the right `workflow_dispatch` inputs\\n- `mise-tasks/test/e2e/_default` — already supports `--agent` and filter args\\n\\n## SKILL.md Structure\\n\\n### Frontmatter\\n```yaml\\nname: e2e-triage\\ndescription: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise or via CI re-runs, classify flaky vs real bug, create PRs for flaky fixes and GitHub issues for real bugs\\n```\\n\\n### Mode Detection (new section)\\n- **CI mode**: `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` env var is set (from `e2e-triage.yml`)\\n- **Local mode**: User invokes `/e2e-triage` manually — no `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID`\\n\\n### Local Mode Steps\\n\\n1. **Parse user input**: test name, agent (optional), or artifact path\\n2. **First run**: `mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>` — capture artifact dir from output\\n3. **If test fails**: Run a **second time** with same params\\n4. **If results split** (1 pass, 1 fail): Run a **third time** as tiebreaker\\n5. **Collect results**: `(test, agent, run_1_pass/fail, run_2_pass/fail, [run_3])`\\n6. Proceed to shared analysis/classification steps\\n\\nNote: Include cost warning — real E2E tests consume API tokens. Confirm with user before running unless specific test names were provided.\\n\\n### CI Mode Steps\\n\\n1. **Download artifacts** from failed run (existing `scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh`)\\n2. **Identify failures** from `report.nocolor.txt` per agent (existing Step 2)\\n3. **For each failing test+agent pair, sequentially**:\\n   a. Trigger re-run: `gh workflow run e2e-isolated.yml -f agent=<agent> -f test=<TestName>`\\n   b. Wait ~5s for run to register\\n   c. Find run ID: `gh run list -w e2e-isolated.yml -L 1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId'`\\n   d. Poll until complete: loop `gh run view <id> --json status,conclusion` every 30s\\n   e. Download artifacts: `gh run download <id> --dir <rerun-dir>`\\n   f. Repeat for second re-run\\n4. **Collect results**: original failure + 2 re-run results per test\\n5. Proceed to shared analysis/classification steps\\n\\n### Shared Steps (analysis, classification, action, summary)\\n\\nLargely preserved from current skill with these enhancements:\\n\\n**Classification gains concrete re-run signals:**\\n- All runs fail with same error → strong `real-bug`\\n- Original fails, both re-runs pass → strong `flaky`\\n- Mixed results (some pass, some fail) → `flaky` (non-deterministic)\\n- Original fails, re-runs fail with *different* error → needs deeper artifact analysis\\n\\n**Cross-agent correlation** uses re-run data instead of guessing.\\n\\n**Summary table** gains a \\\"Re-run Results\\\" column showing pass/fail per run.\\n\\n## Workflow Changes (`e2e-triage.yml`)\\n\\n1. Add `actions: write` to permissions (needed for `gh workflow run`)\\n2. Increase `timeout-minutes: 30` → `timeout-minutes: 60`\\n3. Update Claude prompt to mention re-run capability and the `e2e-isolated.yml` workflow\\n4. No changes to `allowedTools` — `Bash(gh *)` already covers `gh workflow run`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. **Read the updated SKILL.md** and verify both modes are clearly documented\\n2. **Local mode smoke test**: Invoke `/e2e-triage TestSomeTest --agent vogon` and verify it runs `mise run test:e2e:canary` (vogon = canary, no API cost)\\n3. **CI workflow validation**: Check that `e2e-triage.yml` has correct permissions and timeout\\n4. **Canary tests**: `mise run test:e2e:canary` should still pass (no Go code changes)\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-devenv-cli/8f15321d-2333-415f-a295-a31e4d8776e8.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"16d62e69-2514-496b-a4b1-9ecf1b126ab7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:43:08.415Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: E2E Triage Skill — Add Local Mode + CI Re-runs\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe current e2e-triage skill is CI-only: it downloads artifacts from a failed GitHub Actions run and classifies failures based on static artifact analysis. This has two problems:\\n\\n1. **CI mode lacks re-run verifica